description:
Collecting the DC COMICS-- THE NEW 52 series! After the worst disaster in Legion history, the LEGION ACADEMY must help the team rebuild-- while a threat of almost unstoppable power is rising at the edge of DOMINATOR space! Collects the new LEGION OF SUPER-HEROES #1-7!

Back Blurb

A LEGION MADE NEW

In the 31st century, the Legion of Super-Heroes is just starting to pick up the pieces from their new annihilation, and students of the illustrious Academy are being called up to aid rebuilding. But a new daunting enemy threatens their efforts --- a Daxamite with the unstoppable power of the legendary Superman has gone rogue and seeks to start a revolt against the blockade that keeps his race bound to their homeworld. It's up to fellow Daxamite Mon-El, and the rest of the newly re-formed Legion heroes, to ensure that he doesn't unleash an army capable of bringing down the entire United Planets!

As part of the smash hit "New 52" line, LEGION OF SUPERHEROES: HOSTILE WORLD features a broad and spectacular array of heroes. Classic LEGION scribe PAUL LEVITZ weaves together new heroes and old, while artist FRANCIS PORTELA (Black Panther) masterfully brings to life the 31st century and one of comics' most beloved cast of characters- This collection also features a chapter drawn by legend WALTER SIMONSON (WONDER WOMAN), showing an hour-per-page day in the life of the Legion of Super-Heroes. Collects LEGION OF SUPER-HEROES #1-7.
name: Volume 1

description:
Collecting the DC COMICS – THE NEW 52 series! When high school student VIRGIL HAWKINS relocates to New York City, he'll have to battle a whole new kind of evil in the form of the Slate Gang, Piranha and more! Collects the new STATIC SHOCK #1-8 – the entire NEW 52 series!

Back Blurb

GET A JOLT WITH NEW YORK CITY'S BLAZING NEW HERO

Virgil Hawkins maybe a small-town kid, but his skills are Big Time. For he is none other than the smooth-talking, energy-manipulating teenaged superhero Static!

New Yorkers have taken note. So has a consortium of the city's biggest underground bosses. When first the Slate Biker Gang and then Piranha and the Pale Man (looking suspiciously like a certain psychotic clown...) lead an army of pharma-mutated thugs against him, Static and his family are in for a Big City welcome. Still, Virgil can't decide what's more shocking: these new enemies or just how powerful he's turning out too be.

In STATIC SHOCK VOLUME 1: SUPERCHARGED collecting issues #1-8, writer JOHN ROZUM (XOMBI, COBALT) writer/artist SCOTT MCDANIEL (BATMAN, GREEN ARROW) and artist ANDY OWENS (NIGHTWING, SUPERMAN) present Static, the every-teen's stunning new champion!
name: Volume 1
Les Tigres Volants à la Rescousse

description: Writer Daryl Gregory and artist Carlos Magno continue their critically acclaimed run and deliver an arc-ending issue you'll never forget! Alaya must rally her remaining forces against a threat, one even greater than Sully's troop of rebelling humans…one that might come from the highest echelons of Ape society!
name: The Half Man, Part 4

description: The Americans having given themselves the mission to protect the free world, they intend to know everything about everything. So the C.I.A. is angry about not knowing more about C.I.R.C.A.T., a European center that attempts to foil terrorists threats. Believing that Lady S is an occasional recruit of the mysterious organization, the C.I.A. decides to kidnap her adopted father, in the hopes that the young heroine calls the C.I.R.C.A.T. to her rescue thus permitting them to identify some of their agents. So now Suzan is roped into a new adventure, a supercharged road movie across France...
name: Jeu de Dupes

description:
Winter in Stockholm. Suzan is in the Swedish capital with her adopted father, travelling ambassador on a remplacement mission for a few weeks. Suzan is bored ; apart from the nearing Nobel Prize ceremony, distractions are non-existant and nights never-ending.

But very soon, familiar faces start showing up. Orion first, the representative of a mysterious counter-terrorist agency. Then, Anton Grivenko, her old companion from a past she'd rather forget. Orion "forces" the two of them to steal documents from a rich Pakistani's hotel room. The operation is successful and the documents reveal an incredible plot to kidnap the Nobel winners!
name: 59° Latitude Nord

description: Will her past haunter her forever? Lady S remembers her unexpected arrival at the Fitzroy's to return the jewels she stole from them a few years ago. Her only luggage was her 18 years of age and a weight on her conscience : the suicide of a woman who was wrongfully accused in her stead... Shania had decided to put an end to this miserable lifestyle... A fairytale followed : Shania, now Suzan, works with her adopted father, a high-level American diplomat. But sooner or later, troubled pasts tend to re-emerge for people who'd like to forget about them... Suzan is forced to rob som important papers, locked away in a safe deep inside the Turkish embassy in Belgium. Her accomplice is Anton, an old friend from childhood. A mysterious man is now blackmailing them. Who is he? What is his goal? Compromise Turkey's bid to enter the European Union?!
name: À Ta Santé, Suzie!

description:
Adopted daughter and trusted collaborator of James Fitzroy, travelling ambassador and European special envoy of the US Secretary of State, Suzan is an intelligent, multilingual young woman, living a well-adjusted, perfectly happy life with her attentionate father.

But this happiness is too perfect and hides its share of cracks, pains and mysteries. Caught up by her past, Suzan has no other choice but to take on the most dangerous role of her aldready eventful life, that of Lady S, high stakes spy.
name: Na Zdorovié, Shaniouchka!

description: Initially published periodically in Le Journal De Tintin from August 24 1965 onwards before being collected as album by Le Lombard in 1967 and republished by Les Editions Blake Et Mortimer in 1990. Gerald Forton did uncredited artwork on the first few pages before Jacobs took over.
name: L'Affaire du Collier

volume.name: Les Aventures De Blake Et Mortimer

description: First published in Le Journal de Tintin in 1985, then in album form by Casterman the same year.
name: Vercingétorix

description: First published in Le Journal de Tintin in 1982, then in album form by Casterman in 1983.
name: L'Empereur de Chine

description: First published in Le Journal de Tintin in 1981, then in album form by Casterman the same year.
name: La Tour de Babel

description:
Collecting the DC COMICS – THE NEW 52 series! Introducing the electrifying new villain BRAINSTORM, who is determined to bring Los Angeles to its knees – beginning with MICHAEL HOLT! Collects the new MISTER TERRIFIC #1-8 – the entire NEW 52 series!

Back Blurb

COSMIC MIND GAMES

When Michael Holt lost his wife, his entire world has turned upside down. Out of despair, this genius and Fortune 500 CEO used his wealth to become the technology-powered polymath hero Mister Terrific. But a mysterious, new villain has his slight set on Mister Terrific''s most valuable possession: his mind.

The evildoer who calls himself Brainstrom is causing the IQ levels of Los Angeles' innocent citizens to spike, bringing on wild fits of sociopathic mania; and even with his formidable intellect, Mister Terrific isn't immune. Also, a threat is steadily growing in the ninth dimension --- can Mister Terrific regain control of his mind in time to combat the coming of the terrifying alien Kryl?

As part of the smash hit "New 52" line, writer ERIC WALLACE (TITANS, FINAL CRISIS AFTERMATH: INK) is joined by artists GIANLUCA GUGLIOTTA (Secret Warriors), SCOTT CLARK (BRIGHTEST DAY) and OLIVER NOME (CATWOMAN, ROBIN) as they bring you MISTER TERRIFIC: MIND GAMES, the exhilarating tales of one of the world's most brilliant superheroes. Collects MISTER TERRIFIC #1-8.
name: Volume 1

description: Batman #359, Detective Comics #526

At last - Captain Hook is back! Tinker Bell and Terence travel to a strange forest in Never Land to pick bananas for the Fairies of Pixie Hollow. But Captain Hook and his crew have already plundered the fruit! Yes, they have no bananas! Tinker Bell and Terence must sneak onto Captain Hook's ship and take the bananas back to Pixie Hollow without getting caught!

Featuring four more stories starring Tinker Bell, Prilla, Vidia, and the rest of the Disney Fairies.
name: Tinker Bell and the Pirate Adventure

volume.name: America's Black and White Book: 100 Pictured Reasons Why We Are at War

description: Long Hair and Love Triangles! A fashionable high school girl has a crush on the lead singer of a heavy metal band, but he seems indifferent to her feelings. After attending a concert she meets the lead singer's handsome friend who falls in love with her. It's too bad she doesn't feel the spark for him...

Power Girl may have just defeated Lex Luthor's giant robot, but there's no rest for the protector of Metropolis! When a flaming meteor once again lands in Pa Kent's field, is this just a serious case of deja vu or could there possibly be another visitor from Krypton on earth?!
name: Power Girl, 3 of 3

volume.name: Charles Starrett as The Durango Kid

description:
1. Peach on Earth (a Pfirsich Romme story by Donna Barr)

2. Chris-missed (a Bitchy Bitch story by Roberta Gregory)

3. Merry Bloody Xmas (A Santa Claus story by Colin Upton)

4. 24-12-37 CR (by Mike Dashow)

5. The Dead Mouse (a Rhudiprtt story written by Dwight R. Decker, art by Teri S. Wood)

6. Christmas... (a Shanda the Panda story by Mike Sagara and Mike Curtis)

7. It's the most wonderful time of the year... (by Dan Foley)

person_credits.name: Jack T. Chick
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description:
J.H. WILLIAMS III returns as artist on this new story!

An adventure of epic proportions begins here, with BATWOMAN and the werebeast zealot, ABBOTT, hot on the trail of the urban legend BLOODY MARY. The trail leads to a twisted carnival and an abandoned HALL OF MIRRORS, where they face nightmarish versions of themselves…

Batwoman seeks an unexpected ally: WONDER WOMAN!
name: World's Finest Part I: Blood Tides

description:
Shock follows shock as the team learns that the plant monsters were the creation of POISON IVY!

With deadly toxins in their bloodstreams, THE BIRDS have six months to live – and they’ll be given an antidote only if they help IVY punish those who are despoiling the planet.
name: Heartbreak and Vine

description:
The big finale is here, as CATWOMAN confronts DOLLHOUSE!

Don’t miss the fallout from CATWOMAN’s tryst with SPARK!
name: It's Nice To Have Someone I Can RELY On

description:
BLACK HAND has been freed from the INDIGO TRIBE, and now he’s more powerful than ever!

What horrible plan does he have in mind, and to what lengths will Hal Jordan and Sinestro go to stop it?
name: The Revenge of Black Hand, Part 2

description:
STARFIRE has made it all the way to TAMARAN only to find herself caught between the forces of THE BLIGHT and the political maneuvering of her sister, BLACKFIRE.

How will JASON protect ISABEL on what has become an intergalactic date from Hell?
name: We Are Family--Come On Everybody and Die!

description:
It’s BLOOD BEETLE vs. BLUE BEETLE – with Jaime’s life and reputation as a hero on the line!

The Blue Beetle visits his grandmother and the Khaji Da allows him to reveal himself to her without trying to kill her. It also learns a little about Jesus Christ as he is shown visually all over her home. He stays there until he finds out that his friends Paco Testas and Brenda Del Vecchio are looking for him.

What Beetle didn't know is that Paco was taken in the the D.E.O. and was taken over by the scarab on his heart, and calling himself Blood Beetle. So Blood Beetle uses Brenda as bait to fight the Blue Beetle. The battle ensues and Blue uses self sacrifice to save the day.
name: Blood Beetle

description:
KID FLASH stars in his first solo adventure, racing against time as he deals with the prehistoric trouble the TEEN TITANS brought back from MYSTERY ISLAND!

Note: This story is continued from a back up feature in Teen Titans #11 and concludes in the twelfth issue.
name: When Dinosaurs Walked the Earth (That Would be Today)
